<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Nungon Translation]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=7408&amp;p=31933#p31933"><![CDATA[
Yes, translate the required text without any formatting errors, for your level of localization and send it to Ivo. The DLL once published can be downloaded and copied to the folder: C:\ProgramData\ClassicShell\Languages.<br /><br />Then you need to sign out of your Windows user account and login again, and you will be able to pick that language from the Language tab of Settings.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Fri Mar 24, 2017 7:27 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
